    ∇ STITCHSMALL M;G;P;I;H;H_;N;W;X;dot;oc;Q;V[1]   ⍝Stitch the panes of mosaic 1⊃⍵ into a single grid 2⊃⍵[2]   ⍝Only works for small grids!  Need to do it in Python for big grids.[3]   ⍝B. Compton, 21 Oct 2013 (renamed from STITCH)[4]   [5]   [6]   [7]    M G ← M[8]    ⎕ERROR (IFGRIDEXISTS G)/'Error: grid ',G,' already exists'[9]   [10]   oc ← SAVECONNECTIONS   ⍝Save existing connections so we don't mess them up[11]  [12]   H H_ ← MOSAICINFO M[13]   P←P/⍳N←⍴P←⎕FI((2×⍴P)⍴1 0)\P←⊃H[H_ COL 'panemap']       ⍝Panes in grid[14]  [15]   I←0[16]  L1:→((⍴P)<I←I+1)/L2                                     ⍝For each pane,[17]  ⍝ DOT[18]   Q←PANEPATH (⊂M),(⊂STRIP⊃H[H_ COL 'name']),(P[I]),N     ⍝   name of mosaic grid[19]   W V ← (5↑GRIDDESCRIBE M) PANEWINDOW H[H_ COL 'rowsize colsize'],P[I]  ⍝   window[20]   GRIDINIT ''[21]   MAKEWINDOW W[22]   X←READBLOCK (⊂Q),1,1,(V[3 4]),0,1                      ⍝   Read the pane (no caching)[23]   GRIDINIT ''[24]   MAKEWINDOW 5↑⊃H[H_ COL 'extent'][25]   X WRITEBLOCK (⊂G),V,4⍴0                                ⍝   and write it[26]   →L1[27]  [28]  L2:⎕←'Grid ',G,' created from mosaic ',M,'.'[29]   CLEANUP[30]   RESTORECONNECTIONS oc    ∇